request.description:
The identity service provides a list of metrics and dimensions to be used throughout the analytics ecosystem. It provides a canonical id(identity) for each metric/variable so that you can use that identity in all of the different data platforms(datawarehouse,oberon) and expect to get equivalent data out of each one.
It is also helpful in terms of content aware integrations since it provides the content aware identities and tells the data platforms what underlying data that identity actually maps to. This usually involved reserved variables which are allocated on a first come first served basis for each report suite. This makes it so a hypothetical metric called 'social visits' could be reserved event1 on report suite A and reserved event2 on report suite b. The identity service lets the UIs always use the identity 'metrics/socialvisits' and the data platform(s) will ask the identity service what that id means so it can report on the correct data for each report suite. The mapping endpoints are used to create these mappings. Currently the mapping endpoints do not support classifications, but that functionality is planned. We also do not currently support rationing and mapping reserved variables.

request.description:

It provides a canonical id(identity) for each metric/variable so that you can use that identity in all of the different data platforms(datawarehouse,oberon) and expect to get equivalent data out of each one.
It is also helpful in terms of content aware integrations since it provides the content aware identities and tells the data platforms what underlying data that identity actually maps to. This usually involved reserved variables which are allocated on a first come first served basis for each report suite. This makes it so a hypothetical metric called 'social visits' could be reserved event1 on report suite A and reserved event2 on report suite b. The identity service lets the UIs always use the identity 'metrics/socialvisits' and the data platform(s) will ask the identity service what that id means so it can report on the correct data for each report suite. The mapping endpoints are used to create these mappings. Currently the mapping endpoints do not support classifications, but that functionality is planned.
